china 's citic buy h.k . hotel from cheung kong the peking-own china intern trust and invest corp ( citic ) bought the unfinish citi garden hotel in hong kong from a subsidiari of cheung kong ( hold ) ltd & lt ; ckgh.hkg > for 235 mln h.k . dlr , cheung kong director albert chow said . cheung kong 's subsidiari & lt ; intern citi hold ltd > will complet work on the hotel by the end of 1988 , when it will be hand over to citic . the deal doe not includ the decor or fit out of the interior of the hotel . the 600-room hotel stand on a 26,700 sq ft site on the eastern side of hong kong island .